---
import BaseLayout from '../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';

const frontmatter = {
  title: "Barolo Wine - Expert Guide",
  description: "Discover the best barolo wine. Expert recommendations, tasting notes, and tips from certified sommeliers.",
  pubDate: "2026-01-14",
  author: "Michael Chen",
  authorRole: "Wine Buyer & Contributor",
  keywords: ["barolo wine", "barolo", "wine", "wine guide"]
};
---

<BaseLayout title={frontmatter.title} description={frontmatter.description}>
  <article class="container py-8 max-w-4xl mx-auto">
    <header class="mb-8">
      <h1 class="text-4xl font-bold text-wine-800 mb-4">Barolo Wine</h1>
      <p class="text-gray-600">By Michael Chen, Wine Buyer & Contributor | Updated 2026-01-14</p>
    </header>

    <div class="prose prose-wine max-w-none">
      <p class="text-lg text-gray-700 mb-6">Finding the perfect barolo wine can transform your dining experience. Whether you're planning a special occasion or simply enjoying a quiet evening at home, the right wine pairing makes all the difference.</p>

      <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-wine-700 mt-8 mb-4">Quick Answer</h2>
      <p class="text-gray-700">Start with classic examples from renowned regions, then explore based on your personal preferences. Don't be afraid to try something new!</p>

      <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-wine-700 mt-8 mb-4">Our Top Picks</h2>
      
      <div class="bg-gray-50 rounded-lg p-6 mb-4">
        <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-wine-700 mb-2">1. 2025 Bill Harlan final</h3>
        <p class="text-gray-600 mb-2"><strong>Producer:</strong> Bill Harlan</p>
        <p class="text-gray-600 mb-2"><strong>Region:</strong> Côte de Nuits, Unknown Region</p>
        <p class="text-gray-600 mb-2"><strong>Variety:</strong> Pinot Noir</p>
        <p class="text-gray-700 mt-3">Delicate red fruit aromas with hints of mushroom and forest floor.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="bg-gray-50 rounded-lg p-6 mb-4">
        <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-wine-700 mb-2">2. 2019 Aubert Aubert Pinot Noir Sonoma Coast</h3>
        <p class="text-gray-600 mb-2"><strong>Producer:</strong> Aubert</p>
        <p class="text-gray-600 mb-2"><strong>Region:</strong> Sonoma County, California</p>
        <p class="text-gray-600 mb-2"><strong>Variety:</strong> Pinot Noir</p>
        <p class="text-gray-700 mt-3">Light-bodied with vibrant acidity and a long, refined finish.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="bg-gray-50 rounded-lg p-6 mb-4">
        <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-wine-700 mb-2">3. 2018 Bedrock Wine Co. Bedrock Wine Co. Oakville Farmhouse</h3>
        <p class="text-gray-600 mb-2"><strong>Producer:</strong> Bedrock Wine Co.</p>
        <p class="text-gray-600 mb-2"><strong>Region:</strong> Napa Valley, California</p>
        <p class="text-gray-600 mb-2"><strong>Variety:</strong> Red Blend</p>
        <p class="text-gray-700 mt-3">Rich and expressive with dark fruit character and subtle oak influence.</p>
      </div>

      <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-wine-700 mt-8 mb-4">Expert Tips</h2>
      
      <ol class="list-decimal list-inside space-y-3 text-gray-700">
        <li><strong>Temperature matters</strong> - Serve whites chilled (45-50°F) and reds slightly below room temperature (60-65°F)</li>
        <li><strong>Decanting helps</strong> - Give bold reds 30-60 minutes to open up</li>
        <li><strong>Trust your palate</strong> - The best wine is the one you enjoy most</li>
        <li><strong>Consider the occasion</strong> - Match wine intensity to food intensity</li>
        <li><strong>Ask for help</strong> - Wine professionals love sharing their knowledge</li>
      </ol>

      <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-wine-700 mt-8 mb-4">Frequently Asked Questions</h2>
      
      <div class="space-y-6">
        <div>
          <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-wine-700 mb-2">What should I look for in barolo wine?</h3>
          <p class="text-gray-700">Focus on balance, quality producers, and wines that match your taste preferences. Price isn't always an indicator of quality.</p>
        </div>
        <div>
          <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-wine-700 mb-2">How much should I spend?</h3>
          <p class="text-gray-700">Great options exist at every price point. For everyday enjoyment, $15-30 offers excellent value. For special occasions, explore the $40-80 range.</p>
        </div>
        <div>
          <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-wine-700 mb-2">How do I store wine properly?</h3>
          <p class="text-gray-700">Keep bottles on their side in a cool, dark place (55°F ideal). Avoid temperature fluctuations and direct sunlight.</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <hr class="my-8 border-gray-300" />
      <p class="text-gray-600 italic">Michael Chen is a Wine Buyer & Contributor with WSET Level 3 Award in Wines, Italian Wine Scholar (Wine Scholar Guild).</p>
    </div>
  </article>
</BaseLayout>
